    "title": "South Africa's future just got a lot more positive, Anglo American CEO says",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "CAPE TOWN (Reuters) - South Africa’s future is looking “a lot more positive” since President Cyril Ramaphosa succeeded scandal-plagued Jacob Zuma last month, Anglo American’s Chief Executive Mark Cutifani said on Wednesday.\n“We’ve continued to invest in South Africa, we believe in the future of South Africa and from our point of view it just got a lot more positive,” Cutifani said at a conference in Cape Town.\nCutifani said the new mines minister, Gwede Mantashe, had a “great meeting” with mining companies on Tuesday.\nReporting by Wendell Roelf; Writing by Joe Brock, editing by Louise Heavens\n ",
